Review: Needed more Kevin G!!!!!!!!!!!!! People really don’t know how to act in the movies anymore like what

I’ve put this movie off for YEARS. And two hours before a showing on a snowy NYC evening I decided I’d go and stay for Paul’s Q&A. The projectionist got an iMessage notification during the movie that showed up on the screen. Perfect way to watch a really bad movie 🫶🏻
Didn’t learn a thing about him or music or anything frankly. But it’s a good movie???? Does this make sense?
If there’s one thing about Emerald movies it is they are never consistent that’s for sure.
“A World of Your Own” from WONKA heard seeping through the theater walls during a tense scene and I turned and said “do you near that? That’s Wonka”

I just know Chala had the biggest crush on Timmy during filming. I was smiling and bopping along. Wishing Natalia had a bigger part and BEST cameo by Ellie White! Shocked that this wasn’t filmed in Budapest when I’m 90% sure I clocked a Hungarian flag on a tram. Lost points for fat suit. But I am seated for a sequel.
It was like I was at a theme park on a roller coaster and frankly I thought that was fun! Good for Rose! Ruth was sooooo horrible.
Forgot how…uh…mean they all are LOL
WHAT a wonderfully touching flick. The drunken opening dance number was actually history books worthy wow!! And the Stillman’s gym number ahhhh. This movie really has everything.
